From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Spyros Seimenis <sse@edgeless.systems>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 14:38:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] QemuFwCfgAcpi: re-verify blobs after pointer patching

Add a second VerifyBlobData() pass after all table-loader commands
(Allocate, AddPointer, AddChecksum, WritePointer) have been processed.

The initial verification in ProcessCmdAllocate() checks blob data
before any patching occurs. However, ADD_POINTER commands can modify
blob contents after verification -- for example, shifting an
OperationRegion address field that initially passed the allowlist
check. This is a TOCTOU (time-of-check-time-of-use) vulnerability.

Re-scanning all blobs after the command loop closes this gap.
---
 .../Library/AcpiPlatformLib/QemuFwCfgAcpi.c   | 25 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+)

diff --git a/OvmfPkg/Library/AcpiPlatformLib/QemuFwCfgAcpi.c b/OvmfPkg/Library/AcpiPlatformLib/QemuFwCfgAcpi.c
index cd9586516218067fc8efd0b8d8bf37d23bcda165..d728100e53840731a1b4fd053c40c87ea7e477d8 100644
--- a/OvmfPkg/Library/AcpiPlatformLib/QemuFwCfgAcpi.c
+++ b/OvmfPkg/Library/AcpiPlatformLib/QemuFwCfgAcpi.c
@@ -1767,6 +1767,31 @@ InstallQemuFwCfgTables (
     }
   }
 
+  //
+  // Re-verify all blobs after pointer patching (TOCTOU defense).
+  // ADD_POINTER commands above may have modified OperationRegion address
+  // fields or other AML bytecode after the initial VerifyBlobData() check
+  // in ProcessCmdAllocate(). Re-scan to ensure all data is still valid.
+  //
+  for (TrackerEntry = OrderedCollectionMin (Tracker);
+       TrackerEntry != NULL;
+       TrackerEntry = OrderedCollectionNext (TrackerEntry))
+  {
+    BLOB  *Blob;
+
+    Blob   = OrderedCollectionUserStruct (TrackerEntry);
+    Status = VerifyBlobData (Blob->Base, Blob->Size);
+    if (EFI_ERROR (Status)) {
+      DEBUG ((
+        DEBUG_ERROR,
+        "%a: post-patch verification failed for \"%a\"\n",
+        __func__,
+        Blob->File
+        ));
+      goto RollbackWritePointersAndFreeTracker;
+    }
+  }
+
   InstalledKey = AllocatePool (INSTALLED_TABLES_MAX * sizeof *InstalledKey);
   if (InstalledKey == NULL) {
     Status = EFI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
